RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alberta Stallion Stakes Maturity CENTURY MILE RACE 1 330 Y Dirt CR: 79. Match Race Purse 21000. A MATURITY FINAL FOR THREE-YEAR-OLD AND UPWARD QUARTER HORSES WHO ARE ELIGIBLE TO THE ALBERTA STALLION STAKES PROGRAM. A payment of $200.00 is required at time of entry. Preference guides can be found in the AQHRA Stakes Book. Weight: Three-Year-Old 124 lbs. Older: 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: O SEEYALATER came together with NORTHFORK BOSS away from the gate, gained the lead into the stretch, and drew clear under a confident ride. NORTHFORK BOSS came together with O SEEYALATER leaving the gate, and got by deep stretch for place. DOUBLE CRUISE away well and weakened late. TIMBERS EXPRESS late bid. BEARCAT BILL outfinished. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the rider of NORTHFORK BOSS against the rider of OSEEYALATER alleging interference away from the gate was disallowed after the film review by the Board of Stewards, no change was made to the order of finish.

ENTRY.NAME: Northfork Boss
ENTRY.OWNER: Wills Glenn Stockwell Buckey A and Gehring Delton D

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 19500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $17,500. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $17,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $ 22,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRIGORO settled four to five wide, circled into the lane, took over in the final sixteenth and drew clear. SOFIA D 'AMORE trailed the field, gained closer order in the final turn, dug in from along the rail to earn the place spot. MISCHIEVOUSOFFICER set the pace from just off the rail, was overtaken, and was edged out deep stretch. JOY IN GRACE chased outside, and came up empty in the drive. LIGHT FAST FEET tracked the pacesetter while three to four wide, and lacked a closing response.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Lesser Claiming Races Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Claiming Price $5,000 .
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PERDITION steadied out of close quarter while inside, trailed through the far turn, rallied inside entering the stretch, shifted out to the two path, came under a strong hand ride, and was edged clear. REDNECK REMARK vied inside, slipped to the front in the far turn, produced a mild rally when challenged by PERDITION and conceded. HARD TO COME HOME vied between for the lead, chased the leader into the stretch, and flattened. SILVER SPUN settled five wide and offered a late bid. YORKTOWN vied outside then crossed over quickly to the three path, and had nothing left for the drive. POKER TABLE squeezed out in the early stages, and kept on near the back of the pack.

ENTRY.NAME: Perdition
ENTRY.OWNER: Salt River Holdings Inc and Viking Stables
ENTRY.COMMENT: steadied, trailed, rallied inside, edged clear

ENTRY.NAME: Redneck Remark
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, led, mild rally, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BORKAN hustled outside, moved up alongside COMMON KNOWLEDGE near the three-eighths marker to challenge the lead, secured the lead and won going away. TUCKER TIME unhurried early, drove five wide in the final turn, closed steadily outside, and got up in time for the place spot. ESTIFRAAD tracked the pacesetters early, rallied through stretch, and was outkicked for second. AWHITESPORTSCOAT lagged early, roused inside through the stretch, and improved late. COMMON KNOWLEDGE zipped to the front, lacked the rally needed when joined by BORKAN and faded inside. SMARTY RIVER PANTS chased three wide in the far turn, and was outrun. SHARP DRESSED BEAU reared then started bucking losing the rider, did not finish and was vanned off. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Stewards conducted an inquiry into the start of the race but made no change.

ENTRY.NAME: Estifraad
ENTRY.OWNER: Tornado Racing and Frey Racing Stable

ENTRY.NAME: Tucker Time
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried early, 5w, closed steadily, got up

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR ALBERTA BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,000 (Lesser Claiming Races For $3, 500 (AB $4,500) At Century Mile Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ESCROW STYLE sat in range while three wide, angled out to the five path nearing the stretch and won driving. OMEGASSHOOTINGSTAR vied into the opening turn, set the pace from the two path, rallied four wide at the head of the lane, was outkicked and held for place. HIGH FLYIN TIGER vied inside, dueled in the far turn, was unable to match strides into the stretch and finished third best. MAKE'N TRACKS trailed the field, and lodged a mild bid into the stretch. TRICKY SPEEDSTER went four wide through the opening turn, tracked outside, then asked to quicken through the far turn, but failed to threaten in drive. BETTIN ON BELLE fanned three wide into the opening turn, tracked four wide through the backstretch, and was done early.

ENTRY.NAME: Omegasshootingstar
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, set pace, rallied 4w, outkicked, held

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Special Weight Purse 35000. FOR ALBERTA BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: H K RAPPER was outsprinted in the opening turn, waited for running room in the far turn, drove between a seam between foes, and edged clear. OUR SUNSHINE raced from the back of the pack, drove five to six wide at the head of the lane, and closed with good energy getting up for place. COUNTY WINDS contested the pace from off the rail, gained a slim advantage in the far turn, was brushed just after the three-sixteenth pole and was bested in the final yards. ALBERTA BERBON fanned three wide in the opening turn, disputed the pace from the four path, and came up empty in the drive. SMART DECISION hustled outside, raced wide through the backstretch, and had nothing left in the reserve late. BRYNN'S DREAM stalked the dueling pacesetters from the four path, and lost interest with two furlongs remaining. CAROSWAY chased wide through the backstretch, and tired early.

ENTRY.NAME: Our Sunshine
ENTRY.OWNER: Goldbeck, Ernest D. and Ilene A.
ENTRY.COMMENT: back of pack, drove 5-6w, closed good energy

ENTRY.NAME: H K Rapper
ENTRY.COMMENT: outsprinted, waited, close quarters, edged clear

ENTRY.NAME: Smart Decision
ENTRY.OWNER: Hanna Mike W Hardy Lesley Prolift Crane and B First Racing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 7 7F Dirt CR: 77. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS IN THEIR LAST THREE STARTS OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $12,500. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HENRY'S GAMBLE stalked SHE LOVES WINNIN from the three path, pressed the issue near the quarter pole, overtook the lead and held under steady handling. ADDYDIDIT sat in range while three wide, angled out to the four path at the head of the stretch and was gaining on the leader steadily but missed after a game effort. SHE LOVES WINNIN secured the lead quickly under a snug hold, was joined by HENRY'S GAMBLE but lacked the rally needed and weakened in the late stages. GO MAMA settled outside in the early stages, roused at the quarter pole, and rallied belatedly. SKY DESTINY unhurried early then traveled the widest through the backstretch, and rallied late. SUDDENLY MISTY stalked from the rail, and faded inside. MIDNIGHT GARDEN offered little. FLORIST reserved well off the pace, and lacked a bid.

ENTRY.NAME: Henry's Gamble
ENTRY.OWNER: Elsener Terry Brown James R and Konyk Jr Bill

ENTRY.NAME: Addydidit
ENTRY.COMMENT: in range 3w, angled 4w, gained ground, missed
